<TITLE> Maya verdict set for Feb 14 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 4 (bdnews24.com)  A special court Monday fixed Feb 14 to deliver the verdict in a graft case against Dhaka City Awami League general secretary Mofazzal Hossain Chowdhury Maya and four of his relatives. Judge Md Ashraf Hossain of the Special Judge's Court-5 fixed the date following the hearing. The four co-accused are Maya's wife Parvin Chowdhury, his sons Sajedul Hossain Chowdhury and Rashedul Hossain Chowdhury, and Sajedul's wife Subarna Chowdhury. All five accused are currently on the run. The Anticorruption Commission filed the case with Sutrapur Police Station on June 13. The case accuses Maya and his relatives of illegally amassing Tk 5.08 crore, and concealing information on property worth Tk 6.29 crore. Maya's other son Rifat Sayeed Chowdhury and Rashedul's wife Farhana Chowdhury were originally included in the case, although they were later dropped from the charge sheet. Charges were framed in the case on Nov 27. bdnew
